

	 
      Friendship is a pricless gift, that cannot be bought or sold. But it's value is far greater than a mountain made of gold.   For gold is cold and lifeless, it can neither see nor hear. And in a time of trouble, it is powerless to cheer.  It has no ears to listen, no heart to understand. It cannot bring you comfort, or reach out a helping hand.  So when you ask God for a gift, be thankful if he sends... Not diamonds, pearls or riches, but the love of real true friends. 
     

    
